enhanced_by.reason: The unmodifiableSet method is often used to wrap a HashSet, and hashSet method can be used to create the initial set.
The emptySet method can be used to create an empty set, which can then be wrapped by unmodifiableSet.
If the set needs to be thread-safe, synchronizedSet can be used before wrapping it with unmodifiableSet.
If the set needs to be validated before making it unmodifiable, predicatedSet can be used to enforce the predicate.
